  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 190°C/ 170°C (fan)/ gas 5</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Season the <strong>diced beef</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and give everything a good mix up until fully coated</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643797888981-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643797888981-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643797888981-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643797888981-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1643797888981-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated beef </strong>to the pan and cook for 5 min or until nicely browned all over</p><p>While the beef is browning, peel and quarter the <strong>shallots</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>roughly</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643797896786-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643797896786-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643797896786-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643797896786-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1643797896786-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>browned beef</strong> to a clean plate and return the pan to a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped carrot</strong> and <strong>shallot quarters</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1643797916346-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1643797916346-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1643797916346-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1643797916346-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1643797916346-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>Marmite</strong> and <strong>beef stock mix</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>Marmite stock</strong></p><p>Return the <strong>browned beef </strong>and any <strong>juices</strong> to the pan with the <strong>Marmite stock</strong> – this is your <strong>Marmite beef & onion filling</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat, then transfer the <strong>Marmite beef & onion filling</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, cover tightly with <strong>tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for an initial hour or until the meat is tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1643797925522-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1643797925522-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1643797925522-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1643797925522-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1643797925522-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>Marmite beef & onion filling</strong> from the oven after an initial hour and increase the heat to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Dust your work surface with a generous sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong>, then unwrap the <strong>puff pastry</strong> and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a<strong> rolling pin</strong></p><p>Lay the <strong>puff pastry</strong> sheet over the pie dish and trim off any excess</p><p>Press the edges with a fork to seal the pastry to the dish and put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until puffed up and golden – this is your <strong>Marmite beef & onion pie </strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1643797966594-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1643797966594-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1643797966594-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1643797966594-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1643797966594-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pie is in the oven, boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1643797993588-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1643797993588-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1643797993588-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1643797993588-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1643797993588-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p><p>Add the <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour<strong> boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
